Towards the middle of July, Federer hired Pete Sampras' old coach Paul Annacone on a trial basis to put his tennis game and career back on track.[103] At the 2010 US Open, Federer reached the semifinals, where he lost a five-set match to Novak Djokovic after holding two match points.[97] Federer made it to four Masters 1000 finals, prevailing at the Cincinnati Masters against Mardy Fish.[104]
